Television footage from the scene showed a yellow bus lying on its side surrounded by ambulances, with bodies nearby. MARMARIS Seventeen people were killed and 13 injured when a bus carrying Turkish tourists crashed near the southwestern holiday town of Marmaris, a local governor said on Saturday.Television footage from the scene showed a yellow bus lying on its side surrounded by ambulances, with bodies nearby.The bus had traveled from the western city of Izmir, the governor told reporters in televised comments.